A funeral service is being held for outgoing Auditor-General Kimi Makwetu. Makwetu passed away last Wednesday at the age of 54. He will be laid to rest on Thursday, at the Fourways Memorial Park, north of Johannesburg, in a private ceremony. Below is the live stream for Makwetu’s funeral:  Makwetu has been described as a man of honour who served his country with dignity. AGSA Corporate Executive, Mmabatho Mase Sedikela remembers him as a great mentor and leader. 